# RuneForged Architecture Rules

## Separation of concerns
- Keep gameplay logic separate from UI presentation.
- Keep data definitions separate from runtime system behavior.
- Keep reusable formulas and rules in systems or services instead of duplicating them in scene scripts.

## Preferred project boundaries
- scripts/player: player control, combat hooks, interactions
- scripts/items: item logic, inventory logic, equipment logic
- scripts/ui: menus, tooltips, hotbar, HUD behavior
- scripts/enemies: enemy AI and state control
- scripts/world: interactables, drops, spawning, world reactions
- resources or data: item, rune, enemy, loot, and config definitions
- docs: source-of-truth design notes and technical contracts

## Change discipline
- Extend existing systems before creating parallel systems.
- Do not introduce a manager, service, or singleton if an existing system already owns that responsibility.
- If a design decision affects multiple systems, propose the dependency impact before editing.